article.headline: Tulsa 50, TCU 49
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Pat Swilling made one of two free throws with 3.2 seconds remaining and teammate Scottie Haralson rebounded the miss to give Tulsa a 50-49 victory over TCU Saturday. Swilling was fouled by TCU's Adrick McKinney going for a loose ball under the TCU basket, after the Horned Frogs had stolen the ball from Swilling as Tulsa attempted to bring the ball up-court for a final shot. D'Andre Wright scored 14 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead Tulsa (6-3) in both categories. Kauri Black and Shaq Harrison added nine points each for the Golden Hurricane. Garlon Green scored 16 and Connell Crossland 10 for the Horned Frogs (6-4). TCU allows just 52.8 points per game, third-best in the nation.
